<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871218-0089 </DOCNO><HL> U.S. Closes 3 BanksIn Louisiana, Texas</HL><DD> 12/18/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GOVMTTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)BANKS, THRIFT INSTITUTIONS (BNK) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Regulators closed three banks in Louisiana and Texas, and the Federal Deposit Insurance Corp. helped other banks to acquire them.    The closings brought the number of bank failures this year to 183. The failed banks were:    --USBank, Denton, Texas, whose sole office was scheduled to reopen today as a branch of United National Bank, Dallas. USBank had assets of $88 million and deposits of $84.7 million.    --Bank of Maybank, Maybank, Texas, with assets of $44.1 million. It was taken over by First State Bank, Athens, Texas. First State acquired the failed bank's sole office and assumed its $43.2 million in deposits.    --American Bank of Commerce, Lake Charles, La., whose five offices were to reopen today as branches of National Bank of Commerce of Lake Charles. The failed bank held assets totaling $33.5 million and deposits totaling $34.5 million. </TEXT></DOC>